N2  - The proceedings contain 19 papers. The topics discussed include: a systematic review and meta-analysis of adverse events associated with repeated sessions of tDCS; the anaesthetic-ECT time interval with thiopentone; electroconvulsive therapy may be more underutilized than we realize: data from privately insured Americans; treating treatment-resistant PTSD with ECT: systematic review, proposed mechanism of how ECT might help in PTSD, and how research should move forward?; the resolution of persistent auditory verbal hallucinations after long-term maintenance ECT in a patient with clozapine-resistant schizophrenia; predictors of cognitive deficits in depressed patients treated with electro convulsive therapy (ECT), a systematic review; a two-site, open-label, non-randomized update, suggests focal electrically administered seizure therapy (FEAST) may have a reduced time to re-orientation compared to right unilateral ultra-brief pulse electroconvulsive therapy (UBP-RUL ECT); impact of the change from propofol to ethomidate on post ictal supression during ECT treatment; electroconvulsive therapy in a patient with unrepaired splenic artery aneurysm: a case report and literature review; non-consenting and consenting patients' satisfaction after electroconvulsive therapy; moving toward an evidence-based protocol for electroconvulsive therapy; electroconvulsive therapy in a patient with chronic inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy: case report and literature review; and electroconvulsive therapy in patients with deep brain stimulators: a review of the literature and a case report.
